article.headline: Noll's 14 lead Stony Brook past Northeastern 59-55
article.description: — Dean Noll had 14 points in Stony Brook's 59-55 win over Northeastern on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Noll's 14 lead Stony Brook past Northeastern 59-55
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- — Dean Noll had 14 points in Stony Brook's 59-55 win over Northeastern on Saturday night. Noll also contributed six rebounds and four steals for the Seawolves (12-11, 5-5 Coastal Athletic Association). Aaron Clarke scored 14 points while going 6 of 13 (2 for 5 from 3-point range). Keenan Fitzmorris had 12 points and was 3-of-13 shooting and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line. The Huskies (8-15, 3-7) were led in scoring by Jared Turner, who finished with 15 points. Harold Woods added 13 points and eight rebounds for Northeastern. In addition, Masai Troutman finished with nine points, six rebounds and two steals. Stony Brook went into the half tied with Northeastern 22-22. Clarke scored nine points in the half. Clarke's 3-pointer with 1:19 left in the second half gave Stony Brook the lead for good at 54-52. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
